AC   Q47084;
Achromobactin-binding periplasmic protein precursor.
"Differential expression of two siderophore-dependent iron-acquisition
pathways in Erwinia chrysanthemi 3937: characterization of a novel
ferrisiderophore permease of the ABC transporter family.";
-!- FUNCTION: Binds citrate-or chloride-dependent Fe(3+); part of the
    binding-protein-dependent transport system cbrABCD for uptake of
    the siderophore achromobactin.
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Periplasm.
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the bacterial solute-binding protein 8
    family.
-!- SIMILARITY: Contains 1 Fe/B12 periplasmic-binding domain.
